US #50: Return neighbors when fetching an US/IssueThe response for an UserStory/Issue now contains:nn{n...nneighbors: {nprevious: {nid: ...,nref: ...,nsubject: ...n},nnext: {n... same as aboven}n}n}nnIf there's a neighbor missing the response will contain the empty dict {}:nn{n...nneighbors: {nprevious: {},n...n}n}nnNeighbors are looked up applying the same filters defined in thencorresponding ViewSets and the same ordering defined in those filters ornultimately, in the model's meta. In other words, using the same paramsnyou use to filter the object list, can be used to filter the neighborsnwhen fetching the object's details.n
Merge pull request #28 from ikame/masterUS #50: Return neighbors when fetching an US/Issue

Fix neighbors fetching in user stories* Order the received queryset if it doesn't have ordering.n* Do not order UserStory model by ref because the query:n  `queryset.filter(Q(project__gt=1) | Q(order__gt=2) | Q(ref__gt=26))`n  give the wrong result. We need to use the query:n  `queryset.filter(Q(project__gt=1) | Q(order__gt=2))`n  because in SQL there's no short-circuiting.n

Generic voting applicationThe stars application has been removed in favor of a more generic votingnapplication that works with any model. Starring a project is just anspecial case of voting a project.nnUsage.nnAdd a vote:nnvotes.add_vote(<model instance>, user)nnRemove a vote:nnvotes.remove_vote(<model instance>, user)nnGet the queryset of users that voted an object:nnvotes.get_voters(<model instance>)nnGet the number of votes an object has:nnvotes.get_votes(<model instance>)nnGet the objects of type <model> voted by an user:nnvotes.get_voted(user, <model>)nnThe issues application is already making use of the votes applicationnthrough the following urls:nn/api/v1/issues/<id>/upvote  <- url name is issues-upvoten/api/v1/issues/<id>/downvote<- url name is issues-downvoten

Integration with RabbitMQ and CeleryFirst update taiga-vagrant vm if you're using it, you will have accessnto the rabbit management console at port 8001 of the host machine.nn* Defining tasksn- Tasks must be defined in a `deferred` module of an app, for example,n`taiga.projects.deferred` module.n- Tasks must be decorated and given the name <app>.<task-name>, fornexample in `taiga.projects.deferred` module:n```nfrom taiga.celery import appnn@app.task(name=projects.add)ndef add(x, y):nreturn x + yn```n- Tasks should be at most just wrappers around service functions tonpromote re-usability of those functions from other parts of the code,nsay, management commands and the like.nn* Calling tasksnTasks should be called using one of the three functions defined inn`taiga.deferred` module:nn- `defer`: Use this function if you need to perform some tasknasynchronously and GET THE RESULT back later, for example:n```nresult = defer(projects.add, x=1, y=2)n...nresult.get() # => 3n```nn- `call_async`: Use this function when you want to fire off somentask. No result is get back. For example:n```ncall_async(projects.email_user, user)n```nn- `apply_async`: Is the same as `call_async` but since it's a functionnapplication and you must pass the args and kwargs together as onenparameter each you are allowed to pass celery-specificnextra-options (but bear in mind this is not recommended!)n```napply_async(projects.email_user, args=(user,), kwargs={}, routing_key=tasks.email)n```n

Check permissions when accessing attachmentsAttachment files dispatching is now done through `RawAttachmentView`nview that checks for appropiate permissions.nnWhen using the development server this view just redirects to the realnmedia path of the file.nnWhen using the production server the special redirection headern`X-Accel-Redirect` is used instead to improve efficiency by instructingnthe server to dispatch the file instead of django, but you also need thenfollowing configuration (Nginx):nnlocation /attachment-files {ninternal;nalias /path/to/taiga/media/attachment-files;n}nnIt's recommended to also restrict the direct access from outside to then`attachment-files` directory by using some configuration like this:nnlocation /media/attachment-files {ndeny all;n}n
